<p class="summary"><img class="right" src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/blogs_v3/nyt_universal/apture/apture_promo_video.jpg" alt="Apture Video" />Apture allows readers to dig deeper into a subject without ever leaving the blog post. When you click on any link marked by the icons <img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/blogs_v3/nyt_universal/apture/icon_video.gif" alt="video icon" style="padding: 0 2px;" />,  <img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/blogs_v3/nyt_universal/apture/icon_photo.gif" alt="photo icon" style="padding: 0 2px;" />,  or <img src="http://graphics8.nytimes.com/images/blogs_v3/nyt_universal/apture/icon_audio.gif" alt="audio icon" style="padding: 0 2px;" />, you will be able to view video, reference materials, images and other related media. Please e-mail your feedback and thoughts on this feature to <a href="mailto:apture@nyt.com">apture@nyt.com</a>.</p>
